WEBVTT

00:00.568 --> 00:02.415
Okay where were we?

00:02.415 --> 00:04.362
It was June of 2006,

00:04.362 --> 00:06.659
and life had just taken
an unexpected turn.

00:06.659 --> 00:09.729
Dad, can't you just skip ahead
to the part where you meet Mom?

00:09.729 --> 00:12.084
I feel like you've been talking
for like a year.

00:12.336 --> 00:14.700
Honey, all this stuff
I'm telling you is important.

00:14.789 --> 00:16.226
It's all part of the story.

00:16.300 --> 00:18.287
- Could I go to the bathroom?
- No.

00:19.338 --> 00:23.426
The summer of 2006
was both wonderful and awful.

00:23.905 --> 00:25.490
For me, it started out great.

00:25.512 --> 00:27.529
In fact, day one was amazing.

00:27.607 --> 00:29.783
I'd finally gotten together with Robin.

00:30.296 --> 00:33.363
But while I'd been off having
one of the best nights of my life,

00:34.587 --> 00:37.672
your uncle Marshall had been having
one of the worst nights of his.

00:41.307 --> 00:42.423
So that's it?

00:42.597 --> 00:43.681
We're breaking up?

00:44.355 --> 00:46.180
Marshall, I'm sorry.
I just...

00:46.456 --> 00:49.470
I just need to go to San Francisco
and do this art program and

00:49.475 --> 00:52.420
-and figure out who I am outside of us.

00:53.205 --> 00:55.790
And the only way
that I can do that is if...

00:56.655 --> 00:58.663
if we don't talk for a while.

00:59.457 --> 01:00.553
For a while.

01:01.485 --> 01:03.232
Try never, okay?

01:03.505 --> 01:06.041
You walk out that door,
and we're done.

01:06.307 --> 01:08.730
You're never going
to hear my voice again.

01:09.137 --> 01:10.431
I should call her.

01:10.436 --> 01:11.900
- No, No.
- Ted it is--

01:11.905 --> 01:14.221
If you call her when she asked you not to
you're just going to look weak

01:14.226 --> 01:15.530
and you're going to regret it.

01:15.595 --> 01:19.451
Now, listen, whenever you feel like
calling her, you come find me first.

01:20.008 --> 01:21.910
And I will punch you in the face.

01:22.796 --> 01:24.352
You're a good friend, Ted.

01:26.306 --> 01:27.682
Hey.

01:27.848 --> 01:29.013
So, did you hear the big news?

01:29.017 --> 01:31.192
You mean how Lily and Marshall broke up,

01:31.197 --> 01:34.691
and Lily's gone and nothing else
even remotely important happened last night,

01:34.697 --> 01:36.432
yeah, I think he knows.

01:36.457 --> 01:37.723
Oh, my God.

01:37.877 --> 01:39.913
I-I'm so sorry.
Wh--

01:39.916 --> 01:41.072
What happened?

01:41.307 --> 01:43.143
Well, she left.

01:43.147 --> 01:45.760
And I don't even know
if she's coming back.

01:46.085 --> 01:47.871
I didn't get your message until I woke up.

01:48.257 --> 01:50.460
- Bro, I am so sorry.
- Thanks.

01:50.598 --> 01:52.140
I know it must be tough,

01:52.146 --> 01:55.422
but are you ready to hear something
that will not only make you feel better,

01:55.426 --> 01:57.452
but will actively excite you?

01:57.455 --> 01:58.663
Sure.

01:59.005 --> 02:04.981
For the first time, ever, the three of us
are single at the same time.

02:05.305 --> 02:10.009
I've dreamed about this day, boys,
and it's going to be legendary.

02:10.156 --> 02:12.701
Together, we will own this city.

02:13.106 --> 02:17.141
Anytime a girl wants to get back
at her ex-boyfriends,

02:17.147 --> 02:18.720
we'll be there.

02:18.956 --> 02:22.620
