You are the miserable, whining,
shampoo-sniffing ghost of Marshall,

14:54.988 --> 14:58.321
and frankly, a guy like you doesn't have
a shot in hell with a girl like Lily.

14:58.538 --> 15:01.110
You know who might have a shot
somewhere down the line.

15:01.618 --> 15:02.601
Marshall.

15:02.608 --> 15:04.131
The real Marshall.

15:04.138 --> 15:06.003
But if you go down there
right now like this,

15:06.135 --> 15:08.643
you're going to blow it for him,
and he's never going to forgive you.

15:09.898 --> 15:12.193
Of course, whatever I say,
you're just going to do the opposite, so

15:12.196 --> 15:14.732
have a great weekend.
Good luck screwing up your life.

15:14.788 --> 15:15.872
Come on, Robin.

15:20.217 --> 15:22.323
Is it still okay if we borrow the car?

15:24.007 --> 15:26.571
Bold. Bold to go for the car.

15:30.305 --> 15:31.161
What?

15:31.547 --> 15:33.233
I didn't say a thing.

15:33.706 --> 15:35.480
You think I was too hard on him.

15:35.606 --> 15:37.070
I didn't say a thing.

15:37.076 --> 15:39.390
I can't believe you're accusing me
of being too hard on him.

15:39.406 --> 15:40.881
You're the one who said "tough love."

15:40.888 --> 15:43.431
Yeah, tough love,
not "hand the guy a noose."

15:43.437 --> 15:45.563
Oh, but it's okay
to hand him a nine millimeter?

15:46.465 --> 15:48.852
Yeah, he told me.

15:51.168 --> 15:52.631
So you're a gun nut?

15:52.635 --> 15:54.661
No, I'm a gun enthusiast.

15:54.666 --> 15:56.150
- Do you know how many people...
- The Second Amendment...

15:56.167 --> 15:57.652
- are killed each year in accidents...
- protects my right to bear arms...

15:57.655 --> 15:59.710
All right, all right, all right.

15:59.905 --> 16:01.311
I was too hard on him.

16:02.707 --> 16:03.673
A little.

16:06.896 --> 16:08.763
I'm going to call Barney,
see how they're doing.

16:09.898 --> 16:10.772
Go for Barney.

16:10.777 --> 16:12.103
Oh, hey, where are you guys?

16:12.106 --> 16:15.732
We're at a fundraiser, helping young women
raise money for community college.

16:15.736 --> 16:17.100
Strip club, nice.

16:17.296 --> 16:18.441
Is Marshall okay?

16:18.745 --> 16:20.662
Yeah, he's here and he's great.
Uh, hang on.

16:20.665 --> 16:22.190
Marshall?
Tell Ted that--

16:23.956 --> 16:24.613
Uh-oh.

16:24.617 --> 16:25.722
Already?

16:26.977 --> 16:28.271
What? What uh-oh?

16:28.277 --> 16:29.692
He's gone.

16:29.756 --> 16:30.893
You lost him?

16:30.898 --> 16:32.931
I can't believe this.
He's gonna go down to that hotel.

16:33.108 --> 16:35.413
Crap, you're right. Okay, okay,
here's the plan, here's the plan.

16:35.417 --> 16:37.502
You go down to the hotel and find him.

16:37.507 --> 16:39.600
I'll stay here and get a lap dance.
On three. One, two...

16:39.606 --> 16:40.471
Barney!

16:45.987 --> 16:48.290
Was there a hot tub at your uncle's place?

16:48.675 --> 16:51.062
A really nice one.

16:54.208 --> 16:56.662
Hi, uh, could you tell me
what room Lily Aldrin's in?

16:58.756 --> 16:59.693
Marshall.

17:00.187 --> 17:01.201
Hey.

17:03.205 --> 17:04.333
What happened?

17:04.497 --> 17:07.973
Well, I went up to Lily's floor,

17:07.978 --> 17:09.990
and I had this little speech in my head--

17:09.994 --> 17:14.732
everything I've been wanting to say to her
all summer about love, loyalty, respect.

17:15.008 --> 17:16.381
I knocked on the door.

17:22.726 --> 17:25.211
So you knocked out Lily's new boyfriend?

17:25.218 --> 17:26.109
Yeah.

17:26.397 --> 17:27.911
It wasn't Lily's boyfriend.

17:27.917 --> 17:29.542
What? Who-- who was it?

17:29.547 --> 17:31.411
His name was Joey Adalian,

17:31.417 --> 17:35.023
although he went by a number
of aliases in his years as an identity thief.

17:35.425 --> 17:37.273
Apparently, earlier in the summer...

17:37.636 --> 17:40.733
Oh, this is so embarrassing.

17:40.735 --> 17:43.051
I-I could have sworn I had some change.

17:44.068 --> 17:46.011
I know, I know.
I'm sorry.

17:46.806 --> 17:48.213
Oh, here we go.

17:49.007 --> 17:50.703
No, that's-that's a button.

17:50.905 --> 17:52.320
It was a button.

17:55.376 --> 17:58.390
- Do you, uh, take credit cards?
- Yes, I do.

17:59.108 --> 18:02.482
So Lily's not back in town,
and she doesn't have a boyfriend?

18:02.486 --> 18:03.911
Th-That's good news, right?

18:03.917 --> 18:04.790
Yeah.

18:05.908 --> 18:06.981
I don't know.

18:08.028 --> 18:11.693
Those credit card charges were the only
remaining connection I had to her.

18:12.876 --> 18:15.802
I don't know where she is
or what she's doing.

18:16.997 --> 18:20.602
She was my whole life, man,
and now she's-she's gone.

18:25.007 --> 18:27.873
You know, first day of college, I showed up,

18:27.877 --> 18:33.172
I was so freaked out, and-and I got up
to my room, and there was my roommate,

18:33.848 --> 18:36.281
lying on the bed
with his feet up on the wall.

18:36.307 --> 18:40.620
Had headphones on, big smile on his face
like he just didn't give a crap.

18:41.507 --> 18:42.472
Happy.

18:42.695 --> 18:43.820
Confident.

18:43.827 --> 18:45.420
Not afraid of anything.

18:46.315 --> 18:47.891
That guy was you.

18:48.305 --> 18:50.382
You before you met Lily.

18:52.547 --> 18:53.490
Ted?

18:53.928 --> 18:54.810
Yeah?

18:55.767 --> 18:57.232
I was high that day.

18:57.756 --> 19:00.381
I was. I was so high,
I thought you were the dean.

19:02.708 --> 19:10.103
Wh-What I'm saying is there's a version
of you without Lily, and it's not this.

19:11.208 --> 19:15.453
You can't let Lily steal your identity
the way that guy stole hers.

19:17.725 --> 19:18.860
Okay.

19:20.186 --> 19:22.252
Okay, resolved.

19:22.708 --> 19:25.941
Starting tomorrow,
I'm going to start being okay.

19:26.758 --> 19:28.140
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

19:35.307 --> 19:39.043
But he wasn't,
'cause that's not how life works.

19:39.126 --> 19:41.593
The next day,
he found one of her socks or something,

19:41.597 --> 19:43.383
and we were back to square one.

19:46.105 --> 19:47.863
And then, one morning...

19:47.867 --> 19:50.303
Ted, I think you should see this.

19:51.105 --> 19:52.653
Oh, no, what now?

19:54.505 --> 19:56.991
Marshall, what are you doing?

19:57.708 --> 19:58.652
It's Sunday.

19:59.538 --> 20:00.731
It's pancakes day.

20:05.905 --> 20:10.233
It took him 67 days and
one really disgusting batch of pancakes...

20:15.207 --> 20:16.330
So good.

20:17.007 --> 20:18.090
So good.

20:18.707 --> 20:21.253
...but Marshall
had come back from the dead.

20:21.705 --> 20:24.343
Because while baseball, strippers,
and guns can help,

20:24.647 --> 20:28.440
the only thing that
can really heal a broken heart is time.

20:28.448 --> 20:31.080
# I try to laugh about it #

20:31.088 --> 20:34.633
# Cover it all up with lies #

20:36.266 --> 20:39.471
# I try to laugh about it #

20:39.477 --> 20:43.112
# Hiding the tears from my eyes #

20:43.118 --> 20:49.703
# 'Cause boys don't cry. #

